==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: kvass
<hw>kvass</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Russ.
<ets>kvas'</ets>.]</ety> <def>A thin, sour beer, made by pouring warm
water on rye or barley meal and letting it ferment, -- much used by the
Russians.</def> <altsp>[written also <asp>quas</asp> and
<asp>quass</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kwajalein</ent>⟦br⟧
